Speaker 2: Yes, sir. I need to cancel my prescription, please.

Speaker 1: All right. Let me pull up your account.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, sir. Is your last name Gay, Mr. Gay?

Speaker 2: Yes, Kelton Gay.

Speaker 1: All right. One moment.

Speaker 2: All right, sir. So I do see you are a VIP with us here.

Speaker 1: Do you mind if I ask why it is that you want to cancel?

Speaker 2: Well, I've kind of come into some heart issues, and I can't take it no more.

Speaker 1: So there's no need in getting it.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah. I'm sorry to hear that.

Speaker 1: You know, we can just not bill you or ship this to you for a while, sir, even like six months,

Speaker 2: and give us some time maybe that you're cleared to continue with this down the line.

Speaker 1: Well, I don't foresee that ever happening anymore, boss, so I guess we might as well shut it down.

Speaker 2: Okay. I'll do that for you, sir. Anything else that you need?

Speaker 1: Nope. Is there some way or another you can send me an e-mail or statement that this has been done?

Speaker 2: Just a verbal confirmation, sir, that your prescription is canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay. That's all I need. All right. Well, I do appreciate it. Thank you, sir.

Speaker 2: You're welcome. You have a good day.
